
Q: Write the ARM assembly code to load the numbers stored in num1 and num2, add them together, and store the result in numsum. Use only r0 and r1.

A: 	     .bss
  numsum:    .word
  num1:	     .word
  num2:	     .word

  	     .text
  main:	     ldr r0, =num1
  	     ldr r1, =num2
	     add r0, r0, r1
	     str r0, =numsum
	     
